The Western Cape's Social Development Department received tip offs about a scam involving a person claiming to work for Sassa. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape Social Development Department has appealed to grant recipients to refrain from sharing pin numbers.The department has received tip offs about a scam involving a person claiming to work for the social security agency.The individual would contact beneficiaries, offering R400 Sassa Christmas food hampers, in exchange for survey information .The scam artist then requests the pin numbers of the Sassa card holders.Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says: If anyone phones you during the festive season, requesting your card details and claiming to be a Sassa official, know that they are not. Sassa won t phone you and they will never ask for your pin number. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)